  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionAI-Augmented Business Process Management Systems (ABPMSs) represent new human-centered information systems characterized by great flexibility, autonomy, and huge conversational and self-improving capabilities [1].",
    "In this context, the traditional process-aware Decision Support Systems (DSS) are empowered with new AI functionalities for ensuring quick and quality decisions by understanding and explaining the factors that led to the choices [2].",
    "A huge impulse through these kinds of systems can be given by the adoption of Large Language Models (LLMs) [3].",
    "LLMs are emerging machine learning models showing a great capability to achieve a variety of natural language processing tasks [4].",
    "Given their numerous benefits, these models are increasingly more employed in several contexts [5] promising great benefits for industries and business functions and revolutionizing the way humans interact with management systems [6]."
  ],
